         <div>
            <head>Of <choice><orig>loue</orig><reg>love</reg></choice>, fortune, and the <choice><orig>louvers</orig><reg>lover’s</reg></choice> mind.</head>
         <lg type="sonnet">
            <l n="1"><choice><orig>Loue</orig><reg>Love</reg></choice>, Fortune, and my <choice><orig>minde</orig><reg>mind</reg></choice> which do remember</l>
            <l n="2">Eke that is now, and that that once hath <choice><orig>bene</orig><reg>been</reg></choice>:</l>
            <l n="3">Torment my <choice><orig>hart</orig><reg>heart</reg></choice> so sore that very often</l>
            <l n="4">I hate and <choice><orig>enuy</orig><reg>envy</reg></choice> them <choice><orig>beyonde</orig><reg>beyond</reg></choice> all measure.</l>
            <l n="5"><choice><orig>Loue</orig><reg>Love</reg></choice> <choice><orig>sleeth</orig><reg>slayeth</reg></choice> my <choice><orig>hart</orig><reg>heart</reg></choice> while Fortune is <choice><orig>depriuer</orig><reg>depriver</reg></choice></l>
            <l n="6">Of all my comfort: the <choice><orig>folishe</orig><reg>foolish</reg></choice> <choice><orig>minde</orig><reg>mind</reg></choice> than:</l>
            <l n="7">Burneth and <choice><orig>playneth</orig><reg>plaineth</reg></choice>: as one that <choice><orig>sildam</orig><reg>seldom</reg></choice></l>
            <l n="8"><choice><orig>Liueth</orig><reg>Liveth</reg></choice> in rest. Still in displeasure</l>
            <l n="9">My pleasant <choice><orig>daies</orig><reg>days</reg></choice> they <choice><orig>flete</orig><reg>fleet</reg></choice> away and <choice><orig>passe</orig><reg>pass</reg></choice>.</l>
            <l n="10">And <choice><orig>dayly</orig><reg>daily</reg></choice> doth <choice><orig>myne</orig><reg>mine</reg></choice> <choice><orig>yll</orig><reg>ill</reg></choice> change to the worse.</l>
            <l n="11">While more than <choice><orig>halfe</orig><reg>half</reg></choice> is <choice><orig>runne</orig><reg>run</reg></choice> now of my course.</l>
            <l n="12">Alas not of <choice><orig>stele</orig><reg>steel</reg></choice>, but of brittle <choice><orig>glasse</orig><reg>glass</reg></choice>,</l>
            <l n="13">I <choice><orig>se</orig><reg>see</reg></choice> that from my hand falleth my trust:</l>
            <l n="14">And all my thoughtes are <choice><orig>dasshed</orig><reg>dashed</reg></choice> into dust.</l>
         </lg>
         <note type="translation" resp="#jawalsh">Translation of <title rendition="#i">Rvf</title> 124  by Thomas Wyatt (1521?-1554), from <title rendition="#i">Tottel’s Miscellany</title> (1557).</note>
         </div>
